Merge pull request #124 from harvardinformatics/erikenbody-regroups

update read group naming in common.smk

update read group naming in common.smk

At the moment, the read group string is set by the "run" column. This means that the same library sequenced on multiple flow cells gets treated separately when duplicates are marked, even though duplicate marking happens after merging reads. The correct usage of the read group would set a library string and then the full RG string would be the same value for one library sequenced across multiple lanes. This should lead to GATK and Sentieon both marking duplicates according to the LibraryName column, while retaining the utility of the run column processing each run separately before bam merging.

Adding R function to render the QC html file

The main reason this is done as a script is:
1) snakemake prefers to work with functions that can be passed snakemake params
2) due to the messy nature of paths in rmarkdown documents, one has to get creative
when passing params with paths to the rmarkdown::render command

This seems like a possibly place to break if paths dont play
well when this is ported ot another system

- Added a NJ tree generated from a dist matrix produced by plink 1.9

so for now we install both packages

a notable issue here is that ggtree was not functional in this environment
because 3.0.4 is not avialable on conda, so the tree is base R
and not very pretty

update rule all to only have final html QC output

qc.smk now has the R script for plot generation require input from all
other QC commands, meaning that it requires all other rules to run.
The top level snakemake rule all depends on generating that html

We should consider if the other two rule alls can be omitted
until they are used
